<p>
<uicontrol>Example:</uicontrol> To identify whether a call is executed in the evening or day, you can define the rule (similar to the one listed in the following figure) for the <i>TARIFF</i> trigger in the rules.</p>
<fig>
<!--MMO resource relative URI: ../Graphics/Release_19.6/TOD_default.png-->
<image href="../images/img9yz-09126-ug01-pczza-sp1-tod_default.png"/>
</fig>
<p>If the <i>Time-Of-Day</i> value matches the rule, then the calls are considered to be made in the evening. If not, then the default value (day) is considered. Here, the values 64800000 and 82800000 are of timestamp format in seconds which are compared with <i>Time-Of-Day</i> whose reference is taken from the <i>Event-TimeStamp</i> AVP in the CCR message.</p>
